Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20meanwhile%20said%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bdisagreement%26quot%3B%20with%20Biden%20over%20how%20a%20post-conflict%20Gaza%20would%20be%20governed%2C%20reflecting%20a%20rare%20rift%20after%20weeks%20in%20which%20the%20US%20leader%20has%20strongly%20backed%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20told%20a%20campaign%20event%20in%20Washington%20that%20Israel%20had%20%26quot%3Bmost%20of%20the%20world%20supporting%20it%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20Hamas%20attacks%2C%20in%20which%20Israel%20tallied%201%2C200%20deaths%2C%20mostly%20civilians.%20Hundreds%20were%20also%20taken%20hostage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20they're%20starting%20to%20lose%20that%20support%20by%20the%20indiscriminate%20bombing%20that%20takes%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hamas-run%20health%20ministry%20in%20Gaza%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20more%20than%2018%2C400%20people%20--%20also%20mostly%20civilians%20--%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20Israel's%20retaliatory%20bombardment%20of%20the%20coastal%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20had%20previously%20refrained%20from%20describing%20Israeli%20bombing%20as%20%26quot%3Bindiscriminate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20speaking%20later%20Tuesday%20at%20a%20news%20conference%2C%20Biden%20toned%20down%20his%20comments%20somewhat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20United%20States%20has%20to%20support%20Israel%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20brutality%20of%20October%207%2C%20but%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20safety%20of%20innocent%20Palestinians%20is%20still%20of%20great%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20announced%20that%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20Israel%20this%20week%20for%20discussions%20with%20the%20war%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20president%20also%20dismissed%20arguments%20that%20he%20said%20Netanyahu%20had%20made%20about%20Allied%20forces%20in%20World%20War%20II%20having%20%26quot%3Bcarpet-bombed%26quot%3B%2