d%20be%20made%20of%20natural%20and%20untreated%20materials%20that%20won't%20harm%20a%20rabbit%20if%20ingested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bunny's%20front%20teeth%20and%20back%20teeth%20function%20differently.%20The%20front%20incisors%20make%20a%20snipping%20motion%20for%20chomping%20off%20pieces%20of%20grass%20and%20hay%2C%20while%20the%20back%20teeth%20grind%20from%20side%20to%20side.%20It's%20in%20those%20back%20teeth%20that%20Stern%20most%20often%20sees%20problems.%26quot%3BIf%20they%20don't%20chew%20on%20enough%20fibrous%20material%2C%20their%20teeth%20get%20elongated%20and%20it%20causes%20pain%20and%20can%20actually%20lead%20to%20them%20being%20unable%20to%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChew%20toys%20help%20wear%20down%20the%20front%20teeth%20but%20not%20the%20back%20teeth.%20And%20while%20rabbits%20do%20grind%20their%20teeth%20when%20content%2C%20similar%20to%20purring%20in%20a%20cat%2C%20keeping%20their%20back%20teeth%20healthy%20largely%20depends%20on%20providing%20them%20with%20a%20diet%20that%20contains%20tough%20hay%20and%20grasses%20like%20timothy%20and%20orchard.%20As%20they%20chew%20these%20fibrous%20materials%2C%20they%20gradually%20wear%20down%20growing%20back%20teeth%2C%20like%20a%20nail%20file%20removes%20excess%20fingernail%20growth.%20Help%20them%20keep%20their%20back%20teeth%20healthy%20by%20stuffing%20rolling%20balls%2C%20hanging%20toys%2C%20activity%20tables%2C%20and%20any%20other%20loosely%20woven%20toy%20with%20pieces%20of%20hay%20for%20bunnies%20to%20extract%20and%20snack%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20some%20homemade%20toys%20for%20rabbits%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20our%20experts%2C%20fun%2C%20enriching%20toys%20are%20easy%20to%20make%20from%20items%20you%20already%20have%20at%20home%2C%20like%20paper%20bags%20and%20boxes.%20Their%20suggestions%20include%20the%20following%20items%3A%20brown%20paper%20lunch%20bags%20stuffed%20with%20hay%20and%20greens%20and%20tied%20at%20the%20top%2